This game is supposed to be a satire, meaning that the story is supposed to be dumb on purpose. It is a satire on console wars, anime and otaku culture. After you acknowledge that, you can fully enjoy this game.

[u]Pros[/u]
+ Nep nep;
+ Funny story;
+ Nice anime art;
+ The good ol' turn-based system done right;

[u]Cons[/u]
- The entire story is told through visual novel, no cutscenes;
- The DLCs are more cash-grabs than anything, specially in reBirth 1;
- Many monsters are just a lazy copy-paste with some different textures;
- It crashes after battle, but can easily be solved by turning Windows XP compatibility mode on.
